+    "\n",
+    "This function implements the Romberg quadrature algorithm.  Romberg's method is a NewtonŌĆōCotes formula ŌĆō it evaluates the integrand at equally spaced points. The integrand must have continuous derivatives, though fairly good results may be obtained if only a few derivatives exist. If it is possible to evaluate the integrand at unequally spaced points, then other methods such as Gaussian quadrature and ClenshawŌĆōCurtis quadrature are generally more accurate (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Romberg%27s_method). \n",
